SIMPLE: stigmatical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stigmatical
<hw>Stig*mat"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Stigma</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Marked with a stigma, or with something reproachful to
character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Impressing with infamy or reproach.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot., Anat., etc)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a
stigma or stigmata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Stigmatic geometry</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Stigmatics</b></col></mcol>, <cd>that science in which the
correspondence of index and stigma (see <er>Stigma</er>, 7) is made use
of to establish geometrical proportions.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stigmatically</ent>⟦br⟧
